        "title": "Javafx Table stops responding to binding updates",
        "body": "<p>I have the following callback for a column in a JavaFx <code>TableView<\/code><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class CuePreWaitCallback implements Callback&lt;TableColumn.CellDataFeatures&lt;cObj,String&gt;, ObservableValue&lt;String&gt;&gt; {\n\n    @Override\n    public ObservableValue&lt;String&gt; call(final CellDataFeatures&lt;cObj, String&gt; param) {\n        final Timeline preWait = param.getValue().getCTimeline().getPreWait();\n        return new StringBinding() {\n            {\n                super.bind(param.getValue().getCTimeline().getPreWait().playhead());\n                super.bind(param.getValue().getCTimeline().getPreWait().waitTime());\n            }\n\n            @Override\n            protected String computeValue() {\n                System.out.println(\"Value Called----------------------------------------------&gt;\");\n                return preWait.getAbsoluteDuration().subtract(preWait.getPlayhead()).toString();\n            }\n        };\n    }\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Notice the giant print statement in the middle. All of the sudden, the GUI stops updating when the values change. Note that the values change very rapidly (if that matters). About every 3-5 milliseconds (It's displaying a time). <\/p>\n\n<p>About the <code>Timeline<\/code> class: The <code>getAbsoluteDuration()<\/code> method returns a <code>TimeElapsed<\/code> object, which subtracts the <code>preWait.getPlayhead()<\/code> <code>TimeElapsed<\/code> object to create a new <code>TimeElapsed<\/code> object of their difference. The <code>TimeElapsed<\/code> <code>toString()<\/code> method is then called.<\/p>\n",
